complete testing for both pagination styles and filtering in your GraphQL Playground.

üîé 1. Offset-based Pagination + Filtering
Example 1: Get first 3 posts (no filter)
query {
  getPosts(limit: 3, offset: 0) {
    id
    title
    postCategory
    createdAt
  }
}


‚û°Ô∏è Expected:

3 posts returned

Ordered by createdAt descending

Example 2: Paginate to next set
query {
  getPosts(limit: 3, offset: 3) {
    id
    title
    postCategory
  }
}


‚û°Ô∏è Expected:

Next 3 posts (skipping first 3)

Example 3: Filter by category
query {
  getPosts(category: TECHNOLOGY, limit: 2, offset: 0) {
    id
    title
    postCategory
  }
}


‚û°Ô∏è Expected:

Only posts with category TECHNOLOGY

Example 4: Search in titles (case-insensitive)
query {
  getPosts(search: "GraphQL", limit: 5, offset: 0) {
    id
    title
    postCategory
  }
}


‚û°Ô∏è Expected:

Only posts where title contains "GraphQL"


üîé 2. Cursor-based Pagination (Relay-style)
Example 1: Fetch first 2 posts
query {
  getPostsConnection(first: 2) {
    edges {
      cursor
      node {
        id
        title
      }
    }
    pageInfo {
      endCursor
      hasNextPage
    }
    totalCount
  }
}


‚û°Ô∏è Expected:

2 posts

pageInfo.hasNextPage = true if more posts exist

pageInfo.endCursor contains last post _id

Example 2: Fetch next page using cursor

(Replace AFTER_CURSOR_HERE with value from endCursor above)

query {
  getPostsConnection(first: 2, after: "AFTER_CURSOR_HERE") {
    edges {
      cursor
      node {
        id
        title
      }
    }
    pageInfo {
      endCursor
      hasNextPage
    }
    totalCount
  }
}


‚û°Ô∏è Expected:

Next 2 posts after that cursor

If no more posts, hasNextPage = false

Example 3: Filtering with cursor
query {
  getPostsConnection(first: 3, category: EDUCATION, search: "API") {
    edges {
      node {
        id
        title
        postCategory
      }
    }
    pageInfo {
      endCursor
      hasNextPage
    }
    totalCount
  }
}

